3) For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pair within the window compute: total_points_in_window, anomaly_count (value > p95), earliest_anomaly_timestamp (min timestamp where value>p95), longest_consecutive_anomaly_run_minutes (longest run where successive anomaly timestamps differ by exactly 60 seconds), max_value_in_window, mean_value_in_window.
4) Return a compact table (max 20 rows) with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, p95, total_points_in_window, anomaly_count, longest_consecutive_anomaly_run_minutes, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, max_value_in_window, mean_value_in_window. Sort by earliest_anomaly_timestamp ascending (NULLs last), then by anomaly_count desc.
